ABSTRACT
A computer-implemented system and method for facilitating
interactions via automatic agent responses is provided.
Communication during an interaction between a user and an
agent is monitored and a request from the user is identified
during the interaction. A list of candidate responses to the
request is compiled and provided to the agent. Time is
measured upon providing the list to the agent and a prede-
termined amount of time is applied to the measured time.
When the measured time exceeds the predetermined amount
of time and the agent has failed to provide a response to the
user, one of the candidate responses from the list is auto-
matically selected and provided to the user.
